Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)

The datasets in this directory — derived daily sectoral indicators and
within-day share-transformed series, article-level sector-probability vectors
(lexical TF-IDF and zero-shot LLM classifiers), Toda-Yamamoto lead-lag network
edge tables with false-discovery-rate flags, the world-average input-output
coefficient matrix, input-output alignment statistics, and the 50-sector ICIO
V1 lookup — are licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0
International License.

You are free to share (copy and redistribute) and adapt (remix, transform,
build upon) the material for any purpose, including commercially, provided you
give appropriate credit, provide a link to the license, and indicate if
changes were made.

Full legal text: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode
Human-readable summary: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

Attribution:
  Kim, W. & Erokhin, D. (2026). Replication data for "Qualitative Shock Mapping
  for Quantitative Production Network Models: Evidence from Iran-Related
  Hostilities." International Institute for Applied Systems Analysis (IIASA).

NOTE ON RAW TEXT: Raw article text (titles, article bodies, factual summaries,
opinion/interpretation fields, and economic-subtopic labels) is NOT included in
these files, for copyright and licensing reasons. Only derived quantities and
non-text metadata (publication date, source channel, outlet, publisher
location, URL, war-related indicator, risk type, negativity score, risk order,
classifier confidence, and the 50 sector-probability columns) are provided. The
pipeline can be re-run on independently collected text using the code in
`../code/`.
